While Services provide stable internal networking 
(ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer), they are mostly 
Layer 4 (TCP/UDP). They lack the rich HTTP-level 
features needed for real-world applications, such as:

  *Routing traffic based on hostname 
   (example.com vs api.example.com)

  * Routing based on URL path (/api vs /web)

  * TLS termination and certificate management

  * Multiple services behind a single external IP

Ingress is a Kubernetes resource that allows you to 
define these HTTP/HTTPS routing rules. However, 
Ingress is only a specification — you also need an 
Ingress Controller (such as ingress-nginx, Traefik, 
or HAProxy) to actually implement the routing.

Gateway API is the newer, more powerful, and better-
designed successor to the original Ingress resource. 
It offers stronger typing, better role separation, 
and more advanced traffic management features. 
Many teams are now migrating from Ingress to Gateway API.



